  "texts": [
    "We emphasize that, in the above expression, the summations over k α and k β are restricted to the mBZ, whereas q is summed over all intravalley momentum transfers (i.e.",
    "not restricted to only the mBZ momenta).Expressing Ĥint in the BM band basis is reasonable since it is often desirable to truncate to a subset of low-energy bands (often just the central bands) rather than keep all degrees of freedom up to the plane wave cutoff used to diagonalize H BM.",
    "This is known as band projection.",
    "The:...: ρ 0 notation specifies the interaction scheme, which has to do with the 'normal-ordering' of the interaction.",
    "We defer a detailed discussion of interaction schemes and band projection to Section 2.3.1 and 2.3.2."
